{"text": "manmade snow caves|naturally occurring snow caves|Glacier cave\nthumb|Snow cave, Mount Hood, Oregon\nA snow cave is a shelter constructed from snow by certain animals in the wild, human mountain climbers, winter recreational enthusiasts, and winter survivalists. It has thermal properties similar to an igloo and is particularly effective at providing protection from wind as well as low temperatures. A properly made snow cave can be 0 \u00b0C (32 \u00b0F) or warmer inside, even when outside temperatures are \u221240 \u00b0C (\u221240 \u00b0F).", "embedding": [-0.015370871, 0.046162114, -0.20485678, 0.008420784, 0.012319603, 0.033389248, -0.0051459507, 0.011209572, -0.051025756, -0.04808301, -0.028694367, 0.0038820675, 0.056035098, 0.039761327, -0.034424912, 0.017320585, 0.02954851, -0.014293522, 0.056841042, 0.040547583, -0.06705832, -0.012755822, 0.04872488, 0.01142995, 0.04370817, 0.014805703, 0.08200274, 0.07099777, 0.0008680805, 0.037458252, 0.035931747, -0.016923254, -0.0421771, 0.0033976918, -0.019713352, -0.03604069, 0.05162506, 0.011706938, 0.05956354, -0.02488017, 0.046582486, -0.0040719113, 0.020074343, -0.009218808, 0.039511044, -0.00052275177, 0.03446203, -0.049893394, 0.04307194, -0.012921929, 0.05325921, -0.045112733, 0.038627133, -0.045880772, 0.007613342, -0.029559623, 0.0021526546, -0.0137608955, 0.035841525, -0.024879808, 0.056639265, 0.08569814, -0.048438877, 0.010940836, 0.033968437, -0.0045675095, -0.04208364, 0.036168862, 0.01556178, -0.0031787604, 0.042607423, -0.03602875, -0.008073199, 0.016951969, -0.045637146, 0.011583409, -0.03475717, 0.043168772, 0.0028038921, 0.04914712, 0.04277513, 0.0054776757, 0.03294289, -0.043496195, 0.04422312, -0.0077137547, 0.0058669867, 0.042294543, -0.047084022, 0.067878895, -0.015286513, 0.01199624, 0.039268076, 0.024515701, -0.06578769, 0.060764905, 0.0006068003, 0.048922118, -0.07001056, -0.003982351, -0.015627757, -0.048185054, -0.011057829, 0.05212193, 0.0363839, 0.033804376, -0.036016446, 0.005241