{"text": "Regardless of construction type, the snow must be consolidated so that it retains its structure. The walls and roof should be at least 1 ft thick. A length-wise pit may be dug deeper into the cave floor to provide a place for the coldest air to gather, away from the occupants. the cave entrance may be closed up with chunks of snow to deflect wind and retain heat, although it is vital to prevent drifting snow from completely plugging the rest of the entrance in order to maintain a constant air supply. Some prefer to place a ski pole or a ski up from the cave out through the roof or side wall. This can provide an emergency air hole should the main entrance become blocked. Skis can also be placed to cover the entrance or used to secure blocks of snow at the entrance. A snow shovel should always be kept inside the cave when participants are inside.", "embedding": [0.019706989, 0.0508277, -0.18084398, 0.0038111552, 0.041396484, 0.023683017, 0.037646875, 0.051088188, -0.039522376, -0.0738101, -0.039846424, -0.007282319, 0.039751783, 0.0415085, -0.013897435, -0.029429002, 0.021532485, -0.057063248, 0.07745561, 0.0070218653, -0.057739556, -0.029598324, 0.031958386, 0.0046471194, 0.01275767, 0.003866181, 0.07422463, 0.0348252, -0.0031828904, 0.03466049, 0.042368002, -0.045534007, -0.008732997, -0.037295096, -0.023093918, -0.074571915, 0.049844276, 0.035546128, 0.02062106, -0.056640096, 0.05762489, -0.02490811, 0.009501402, -0.029785225, 0.02777842, -0.009702043, 0.04905631, -0.041927572, 0.050937265, 0.015756717, 0.040857505, -0.047171146, -0.032190587, -0.028998403, 0.021173522, -0.007139583, 0.025644703, 0.0012708069, 0.081511095, -0.03323641, 0.042467628, 0.06806677, -0.04771122, 0.022148393, 0.009880649, 0.008782083, -0.031283624, 0.053314753, 0.009801702, -0.0092421835, 0.059243664, -0.023615766, 0.039071303, 0.015234987, -0.053970397, 0.0026837923, -0.03682062, 0.006082384, 0.010257047, 0.05133815, 0.016854748, -0.0035376272, 0.033532135, -0.03596273, 0.03173